# jfeelgood.com — Landing Page

A responsive, single-file landing page for [JFeelgood](https://jfeelgood.com), an original art brand based in Austin, Texas.

---

## Overview

This landing page is built as a single self-contained HTML file (`jfeelgood.html`). It uses no build tools, no frameworks, and no external dependencies beyond two Google Fonts families. Drop it on any static host and it works.

---

## Structure

The page follows a conversion-focused narrative flow:

| Section | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Hero** | Brand introduction, headline, and primary CTA |
| **Problem** | Why generic art fails — setting up the value proposition |
| **Solution** | What makes JFeelgood's work different |
| **Features / Gallery** | Six featured paintings with titles, prices, and dimensions |
| **Testimonial** | Press quote + full artist bio |
| **CTA** | Final call to collect / purchase |

---

## Tech Stack

- **Pure HTML/CSS/JS** — no frameworks, no npm, no build step
- **Fonts:** Cormorant Garamond (serif display) + DM Mono (labels/eyebrows) via Google Fonts
- **Animations:** CSS transitions + IntersectionObserver scroll-reveal
- **Layout:** CSS Grid throughout; fully responsive at 900px and 560px breakpoints

---

## Image Placeholders

All images are currently placeholders. Each placeholder includes descriptive alt text specifying exactly what image belongs there. To replace a placeholder:

1. Find the `<div class="img-placeholder">` inside the relevant section
2. Replace the entire `<div class="img-placeholder">...</div>` block with:
   ```html
   <img src="your-image.jpg" alt="Descriptive alt text" />
   ```
3. The parent container already has `overflow: hidden` and sizing — the image will fill it automatically. Add `style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;"` to the `<img>` tag for best results.

### Placeholder inventory

